# Cross-platform portability

Capacitor implementation is paused while the Web product workflow is completed.
Do not install Capacitor packages, create native projects, or implement native
adapters until the user explicitly resumes that workstream.

The product must remain shippable as Web, iOS, and Android from one shared
business-logic codebase. Web should prioritize data presentation, historical
review, analytics, comparison, and reporting.

Every feature, fix, and refactor, including vibe coding, must comply with
`docs/CROSS_PLATFORM_VIBE_CODING_GUARDRAILS.md`.

Browser and device access belongs behind `lib/platform` ports. Shared
components, hooks, domain code, synchronization code, and data services must not
acquire browser-only assumptions or import `@capacitor/*`.

